% issue: a whole measure sitting entirely on staff 2 (after a prior staff-2
% voice) with a genuine clef change. The .lyl serializer must emit an explicit
% \staff "2" anchor even though the cross-measure carry already equals 2 — the
% parser defaults a directive-less voice to staff 1, so without the anchor the
% voice and its clef would be relocated to staff 1 on re-parse.
\staff "1" \clef "treble" \time 2/4 c''4 c'' \\
\staff "2" \clef "bass" c4 c | %1
\staff "2" \clef "treble" c'4 c' | %2
